<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:27PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN RUTHERFORD AND
NORTHWESTERN CLEVELAND COUNTIES THROUGH 400 PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Forest City, or 6 miles north of Bostic, moving east
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Polkville, Casar, Sunshine, and Union Mills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
